The paper deals with natural language processing and information retrieval tasks such as set expansion, which are typically covered under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes an unsupervised framework for facet discovery and entity expansion, which involves clustering and optimization techniques, respectively, that are commonly used in database systems (cs.DB).
